        "description": "Add an asymmetry/shape parameter c5 as an exponent on the logistic denominator: y = c4 / (1 + exp(-c0 * x1^c1 * (x0 - c2 * x1^c3)))^c5 + c6. This is the Richards model, which reduces to the standard logistic when c5=1. Protein aggregation curves are often asymmetric (slow nucleation, fast growth phase), so this single additional parameter can substantially improve fit quality across many datasets.",
